Clarence S. HOWE, Immigration Inspector in charge at Victoria, Texas, Appellant, v. Maria GONZALEZ, Alias Rangel, Alias Diaz, Appellee. No. 8796. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Dec. 5, 1938. Douglas W. McGregor, U. S. Atty., and George P. Red, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Houston, Tex., for appellant. Eugene J. Wilson, of Bay City, Tex., for appellee.

Before SIBLEY, HOLMES, and McCORD, Circuit judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
